<p><strong>STAAR Reading Grade 4: Forde and Ferrier PDF</strong></p>
<p>The STAAR (State of Texas Assessments of Academic Readiness) Reading Grade 4 exam, developed by Forde and Ferrier, assesses students' reading comprehension and critical thinking skills. The exam is divided into multiple sections, each with specific questions. This article provides answers to commonly asked questions about the exam.</p>
<p><strong>Section 1: Literary Text</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Question:</strong> What is the main idea of the passage about the life cycle of a butterfly?</li>
<li><strong>Answer:</strong> The main idea is that the life cycle of a butterfly has four stages: egg, larva, pupa, and adult.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Section 2: Informational Text</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Question:</strong> According to the passage, why is it important to reduce, reuse, and recycle?</li>
<li><strong>Answer:</strong> Reducing, reusing, and recycling helps conserve natural resources, reduces pollution, and saves energy.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Section 3: Multiple-Choice Questions</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Question:</strong> Which of the following words best describes a story that has a happy ending?</li>
<li><strong>Answer:</strong> Joyful</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Section 4: Open-Ended Response</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Question:</strong> Write a short paragraph explaining how the character in the story "The Great Race" overcame a challenge.</li>
<li><strong>Answer:</strong> The Great Race; The character in the story faced a challenge when The character's wagon wheel broke. The character worked hard to fix the wheel and used a tree limb to help it turn. This allowed The character to overcome the challenge and win the race.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Section 5: Revising and Editing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Question:</strong> Which of the following sentences is written correctly?</li>
<li><strong>Answer:</strong> The dog barked loudly at the mailbox.</li>
</ul>